olive oil
1 Parsnip
1 Beetroot
½ Onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 Silverbeet
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Pork Schnitzels
2 tbs plain flour
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
15 g butter
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet creamy pesto dressing

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks. Slice red onion into wedges.
• Place parsnip, beetroot, red onion and peeled & chopped pumpkin on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop silverbeet. Finely chop garlic.
• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and a pinch of salt. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, place panko breadcrumbs and Nan's special seasoning.
• Dip pork into flour mixture to coat, followed by the egg, and finally in breadcrumbs. Set aside on a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the silverbeet and the butter and cook until tender,
2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste and transfer to a bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover base.
• Cook pork schnitzel in batches until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Ensure the oil is hot before cooking the pork schnitzels for best results!

• When the roasted veggies are done, remove tray from oven, add buttered silverbeet and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice pork.
• Divide brown butter root veggie toss between plates.
• Top with Nan's crumbed pork.
• Drizzle over creamy pesto dressing to serve. Enjoy!